reply_text:
@ThisIsWideAngle I agree with you - I haven't seen much, if any of his silly stuff (the Happy Gilmore, Little Nicky, Big Daddy etc genres) as it's not my thing either. 
I'm more a fan of the rom-coms 'cuz he brings a certain charm to his characters in those movies. 
Whenever I find someone who says they can't stand Sandler, our go-to movie is The Wedding Singer. That movie has never failed yet to convert a non-believer. His range is subtle, but it's there and it hits all the spots; he's quite vulnerable in that role, too - so you can see the potential for a decently serious actor in there.
